At least 41 people were killed after a bus skidded into a ravine near Karachi, Pakistan on Sunday morning, Dawn News reported. The coach, carrying nearly 48 passengers, was travelling from Quetta to Karachi. "Due to speeding, the coach crashed into the pillar of a bridge while taking a U-turn near Lasbela. The vehicle subsequently careened into a ravine and then caught fire," Lasbela Assistant Commissioner Hamza Anjum was quoted as saying in the report.